$ SQLite: drop view
@ drop view

{ Dropping a view only if it exists #drop-view-if-exists

  In order to suppress error messages, → development/databases/SQLite supports the `drop view if exists` clause which only tries to drop a → development/databases/SQLite/views[view] if it in fact *does* exist:
  gh|about-sqlite|/views/drop_if_exists.sql||

  See als → development/databases/SQLite/tables/drop#drop-table-if-exists

}

sa:
  → development/databases/SQLite/views
